Really enjoyed this. As others have said, the restraint shown here in the description makes it a lot better. Less is more and all. There's a lot to be read into this between the lines. My only suggestion for improvement would be perhaps giving a bit more detail on the mask in the containment procedures(maybe they stored it or are studying it) and the early description. It's a good ending for the mask to be removed before it perished, but it might hit harder if we could imagine it as more than silicon polymers in the shape of a breathing mask. Other than that I don't have any complaints for this one. Really good picture choice as well. +1








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






